<br /><br /></p>

<p>|Data Types Categories|Types|
|-|-|
|Text types|str|
|Numeric Types|int, float, complex|
|Sequence Types|list(mutable)<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">[0,1]</code>, tuple(immutable)<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">(0,1)</code>, range|
|Mapping Type|dict <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{"key":"value"}</code>|
|Set Types|set, frozenset <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">{0,1,2,3}</code>|
|Boolean Type|bool <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">True False</code>|
|Binary Types|bytes, bytearray, memoryview|
<br /><br /></p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Data type of any object can be obtained by using the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">type()</code> function</p>
</blockquote>

